    • Field Detail

      • CONTINUE

        public static final int CONTINUE
        Indicates that the request processing should continue normally. If returned from the evaluateOnRequest(org.forgerock.json.resource.ServerContext, org.forgerock.openidm.core.filter.ScriptedFilter.ScriptState) method, the filter then invokes the CrossCutFilterResultHandler.handleContinue(org.forgerock.json.resource.ServerContext, Object) method.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • SKIP

        public static final int SKIP
        Indicates that after the evaluateOnRequest(org.forgerock.json.resource.ServerContext, org.forgerock.openidm.core.filter.ScriptedFilter.ScriptState) method, the request processing should skip the CrossCutFilterResultHandler.handleContinue(org.forgerock.json.resource.ServerContext, Object) method to continue with the RequestHandler method.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values

      • STOP

        public static final int STOP
        Indicates that the request processing should stop and return the current response from the filter.
        See Also:
        Constant Field Values
